Vice President Mike Pence visited Yellowstone National Park to express appreciation for the work being done to preserve and protect the park. He commended Secretary of the Interior David Bernhardt for his efforts in managing the country's natural resources. Pence highlighted the importance of national parks and encouraged Americans to visit Yellowstone. He also recognized the park's superintendent, Cam Sholly, and thanked the congressional delegation for their support. Pence emphasized President Donald Trump's commitment to conservation and mentioned the proposed Public Lands Infrastructure Fund. He pledged continued support for the National Park Service and expressed gratitude to all the park employees for their dedication. Pence's wife, Karen Pence, praised the Artist-in-Residence program and recognized a watercolor artist currently at the park. Pence concluded by emphasizing the role of stewardship in preserving the country's natural treasures.